column23: fig 1 p 69: LTF Operated with SGN= 103 Operated with MSP=108  Died before 4 month f/u: SGN=11, MSP=22  Lost at 4 mo f/u: other than died SGN=11, MSP=5  cumulative diedbefore 12 mo f/u: SGN=24, MSP=31  Additional LTF at 12 mo (bt/w 4-12 mo): SGN=3, MSP=3  Available at 12 month for f/u: SGN=82, MSP=74  NOTE-Intention to treat: randomized but treated differently: "Operative data. Six patients in the SGN group were operated on using a method of variance with the randomisation (Fig. 1). Three of these sustained an intra-operative femoral fracture. In two this was caused by an inadequate surgical technique. In spite of the recommended operative technique, a hammer had been used during insertion of the nail in one patient and in the other a wrong entry point had been used leading to excessive force during insertion of the nail. The intra-operative fractures were all recognised during during the primary procedure and the SGN was exchanged in all cases to a long gamma nail (LGN) with uneventful outcomes. In two patients an LGN had been used because of misinterpretation of the study protocol by the surgeons. Finally, in one case the surgeon considered open reduction to be necessary and therefore intra-operatively changed the SGN to an MSP."

column23: Mortality: "Two patients in Group A and three patients in Group B died during their hospital stay."...and "The mortality was high in both groups, but did not differ significantly between them. At 3 months, five patients in Group A and four patients in Group B had died. At 6 months, six patients in Group A and seven patients in Group B had died. After 1 year, nine patients in Group A and seven patients in Group B had died; and after 2 years, 12 patients in Group A and 11 patients in Group B had died." OTHER LTF -I cannot tell at what point in 3 yr followup that this was actually assessed.  It may describe 1 pt LTF at 1 yr(alive at 1 yr=64), which makes me wonder how many were actually followed for 3 yrs, since no Table data extend out that far: "Among these patients (30 in Group A and 34 in Group B), one patient in Group B was lost to followup because she was incarcerated."  NOTE: one less pt in Table values for Group 2: "In one patient in Group B, a dynamically locked nail was used but erroneously locked with two screws.
